x=\dfrac{4ab}{a+b} \implies \dfrac x {2a} = \dfrac {2b} {a+b} \;\; and \;\; \dfrac x {2b} = \dfrac {2a}{a+b}  
\dfrac{x+ 2a}{x-2a} = \dfrac{3b + a}{b - a} \;\; and \;\;  \dfrac{x+ 2b}{x-2b} = \dfrac{3a + b}{a - b}
a\neq b
\dfrac{3b + a}{b-a} + \dfrac{3a + b}{a - b} = \dfrac{2(a - b)}{a - b} = 2
a, b \neq 0
x
\frac{x+2a}{x-2a}+\frac{x+2b}{x-2b} =\frac{\frac{4ab}{a+b}+2a}{\frac{4ab}{a+b}-2a}+\frac{\frac{4ab}{a+b}+2b}{\frac{4ab}{a+b}-2b}\\ =\frac{2a(3b+a)/(b+a)}{-2a(a-b)/(b+a)} + \frac{2b(3a+b)/(b+a)}{2b(a-b)/(b+a)}\\ =-\frac{3b+a}{a-b} + \frac{3a+b}{a-b}\\ = \frac{-3b - a +3a + b}{a-b} = \frac{-2b + 2a}{a-b} = 2 
